title: For Sale:  WWI French Mle 1892 revolver + orig. holster and ammo
postcontent: For sale is a World War I war horse. A model 1892 French Revolver in 8mm French. EXCELLENT original condition. Dated 1899. Cylinder timing is perfect. Functions smoothly and strongly with crisp trigger pull like a modern revolver. Sights are unique to this model and very good for target aquisition. These were favorites of the French Foreign Legion before, during and after WWI, as well as French Resistance fighters and some Nazi soldiers during World War II. In fact, a few days ago a cache buried in Latvia during WWII was discovered with a preserved Mle 1892 revovler just like the one offered here. The revolver, along with other supplies and explosives, was left for saboteurs in the area! (article is on guns.com and is titled "70 year old saboteur cache looks like it was buried yesterday (17 PHOTOS)").Lots of history and a good shooter! Ammo can be reloaded or purchased from a few places online. -Comes with the original holster which is in great condition as well. The leather is very supple, strong and flexible and can still be worn or hung on a belt for display.-Also included is a rare box of original unfired ammo! ActionChamber:                .45 ACPWeight Unloaded:    1400 gramsLength:                   212 mmBarrel Length:         116 mmCapacity:                12 rounds + 1 in chamberThe MegaStar pistol is a heavy, powerful pistol, which appeared on the markets in 1993.  It was designedand manufactured by the Spanish company Star Bonifacio SA, and its design is based on the previous guns by the same manufacturer, such as Star 30M.   Production of the MegaStar was completed in late 1990s.Megastar is recoil operated, locked breech semi-automatic pistol.  It uses a Browning High-Power type locking system with tilting barrel.  Megastar is a hammer fired pistol, with double action trigger and ambidextrous, slide mounted safety-decocker lever.  The safety lever has three position:  upper one for "fire" mode, red dot is shown, medium one for "safe" mode, this withdraws and locks the firing pin, and the lower one for safe decocking (after decocking safety lever springs back to the "safe" position).  Megastar also features a magazine disconnect safety which does not allow to fire the gun without magazine in the place.  Megastar slide and frame are made from all steel, and like other latest Star pistols.  Megastar has internal slide rails, instead of more usual external rails.  This pistol features non-adjustable sights.  Magazine capacity is quite impressive, especially when speaking about the period of the early 1990s, and is 12 rounds of .45 ACP.  Overall, Megastar represents one of the strongest designs in auto-pistols, heavy but powerful and built to last forever.  Heavy weight also helps to control the recoil of the powerful cartridges used.
